Bring a pan of salted water to the boil, add the potatoes and boil for 8-10 minutes, or until tender.Add the fresh peas to the pan for the final three minutes of cooking time and drain.In a bowl, mix the potatoes and peas with the walnuts and crumble in the goats' cheese.In another small bowl, mix the Greek-style yoghurt with the herbs, season with salt and freshly ground black pepper and drizzle over the salad.Serve.